1️⃣ Upgrade the Offer Name (Huge Impact)

“Strategy Call” is neutral.

We want outcome-focused.

Replace:

❌ First-Time Buyer Strategy Call
With one of these:

✅ Under-$500K Game Plan Session
✅ PSL Homebuyer Clarity Session
✅ First-Time Buyer Roadmap Call
✅ Your Personalized PSL Buying Plan

My recommendation:

👉 “Under-$500K Homebuyer Game Plan Session”

It sounds specific. Valuable. Strategic.

⸻

2️⃣ Add Urgency Without Pressure

On your thank-you page, change:

“Book your strategy call”

To:

“Reserve Your Under-$500K Game Plan Session (Limited Weekly Spots)”

Scarcity increases booking rate 15–30%.

You can even add:

“I only take 5 first-time buyer sessions per week.”

Specific = believable.

⸻

3️⃣ Reduce Calendar Friction

Most booking loss happens here.

Optimize your calendar page:

• Add a short video at the top:
“Here’s what we’ll cover in 15 minutes…”

• Add 3 bullet outcomes:

After this call, you’ll know:
✔ What you likely qualify for
✔ Which PSL neighborhoods fit your budget
✔ Whether now makes sense for you

• Remove unnecessary intake fields
Keep it to:
– Name
– Email
– Timeline
– Are you pre-approved?

Less friction = more bookings.

⸻

4️⃣ Install the “Micro Yes” Text Trigger

Instead of sending booking link immediately via text, try this:

Text:

“Would it make sense to map this out together for 15 minutes?”

Wait for yes.

When they say yes, THEN send link.

That micro-commitment dramatically increases show-up rate.

⸻

5️⃣ Add a 3-Minute Fast Track Option

On thank-you page, add this:

“Not ready to book a call?
Answer 3 quick questions and I’ll send you a personalized plan.”

Mini form:
• Budget range
• Timeline
• New or resale
• Renting or owning now

This converts hesitant leads who aren’t ready for a call.

⸻

6️⃣ Add Immediate SMS After Booking

Once they schedule:

Text immediately:

“Excited to connect [Name]. Quick prep question: what’s your biggest concern about buying right now?”

This increases show rate and emotional engagement.

⸻

7️⃣ Add a Deadline Angle (Ethical Scarcity)

You can say:

“Under-$500K inventory shifts quickly. Buyers who plan early secure better terms.”

Not panic.

Preparation.

⸻

